HEADWORD: Arbitrament
<hw>Ar*bit"ra*ment</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>arbitramentum</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Determination;
decision; arbitration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>arbitrament</qex> of time.</q>
<rj><qau>Everett.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Gladly at this moment would MacIvor have put their quarrel to
personal <qex>arbitrament</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The award of arbitrators.</def>
<rj><au>Cowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arbitrarily</ent>⟦br⟧
